{
  "stem": "13313.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and we talked to neighbors and we met all kinds of people, the local policeman, and the-- and the shepherd, and-- and the people in all the stores that we want to shop.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And some people were collaborators with the Germans and some were not.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We never knew who was who, so we had to be very, very careful not to give ourselves away.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so most of the-- so it was ironic.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I would say that she, Mrs.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Roggeman, was probably the worst person in terms of-- of evil that I encountered during that war.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because I physically experienced her physical abuse.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But almost unbelievably, despite of everything that happened by the Germans, I would have to say that the nicest person that I met in World War II happened to be a German officer.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "A German officer was the nicest person I met in World War II.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It so happened that there was a German major of the German Transportation Division of the Wehrmacht who had been a friend of the Roggemans before they took us in hiding.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the way he became a friend was that the Germans occupations, they-- whenever there was people had a free room or didn't have kids, they would billet their officers in private homes.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he was billeted with the Roggemans prior to us being taken in by them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he knew that they had no children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was a friend of the house, and he continued to visit even after.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, he used to come over on the train and then jump off just in front of the house where we were.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So he knew that we were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
